**Add New Move**

Move Scripting System Documentation (can be used as a guide for Platinum): https://github.com/BluRosie/hg-engine/wiki/Move-Scripting-Systems-Documentation

1. Add the new move ID  
Path: [moves.txt](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/generated/moves.txt)  
Action: add `MOVE_PLASMA_BURST` right before `MAX_MOVES`.

2. Make a folder for the move  
Path: `C:\Users\tinle\Downloads\pokeplatinum\res\battle\moves\plasma_burst`  
Action: copy a similar move folder (example: `thunderbolt`) and rename to `plasma_burst`.

3. Edit move stats/data  
Path: [plasma_burst/data.json](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/res/battle/moves/plasma_burst/data.json)  
Action: set name, type, power, accuracy, pp, flags, etc.  

4. Edit animation script  
Path: [plasma_burst/anim.s](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/res/battle/moves/plasma_burst/anim.s)  
Action: copy/tweak animation commands from a similar move.

5. Build just move data + animation  
Run from repo root:
```bash
ninja -C build res/battle/moves/pl_waza_tbl.narc
ninja -C build res/battle/moves/anim_scripts.narc
ninja -C build pokeplatinum.us.nds
```

---

**B) Only if you need brand-new move behavior: add a new effect script**

6. Add a new effect enum name  
Path: [battle_move_effects.txt](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/generated/battle_move_effects.txt)  
Action: append `BATTLE_EFFECT_PLASMA_BURST`.

7. Create the new effect script file  
Path: pokeplatinum\res\battle\scripts\effects\effect_script_0259.s` (use next free number) 

8. Register that new effect script in build file  
Path: [effects/meson.build](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/res/battle/scripts/effects/meson.build)  
Action: add `effect_script_0259.s` to `effect_script_files`.

9. Point your move at this new effect  
Path: [plasma_burst/data.json](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/res/battle/moves/plasma_burst/data.json)  
Action: set `"effect.type": "BATTLE_EFFECT_PLASMA_BURST"`.

10. Rebuild effect script archives
```bash
ninja -C build res/battle/scripts/be_seq.narc
ninja -C build res/battle/scripts/waza_seq.narc
ninja -C build pokeplatinum.us.nds
```

---
Adding new subscripts:

11. Add subscript enum  
Path: [battle_subscripts.txt](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/generated/battle_subscripts.txt)  
Action: append `BATTLE_SUBSCRIPT_PLASMA_BURST`.

12. Create subscript file  
Path: `C:\Users\tinle\Downloads\pokeplatinum\res\battle\scripts\subscripts\subscript_plasma_burst.s`

13. Register subscript in build list  
Path: [subscripts/meson.build](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/res/battle/scripts/subscripts/meson.build)  
Action: add `subscript_plasma_burst.s` to `subscript_files`.

14. Register subscript order  
Path: [sub_seq.order](/C:/Users/tinle/Downloads/pokeplatinum/res/battle/scripts/subscripts/sub_seq.order)  
Action: add `subscript_plasma_burst` (no `.s`).

15. If your effect uses `MOVE_SUBSCRIPT_PTR_`, add pointer enum  
Path: [battle_move_subscript_ptrs.txt](pokeplatinum/generated/battle_move_subscript_ptrs.txt)  
Action: append `MOVE_SUBSCRIPT_PTR_PLASMA_BURST`, then reference it in your effect script.

16. Rebuild subscript archive
```bash
ninja -C build res/battle/scripts/sub_seq.narc
ninja -C build pokeplatinum.us.nds
```

